This is a request to add the colon punctuation mark (:) to the list of special characters supported for text searching. Refer to JRA-23519 (http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-23519) for more details. In short, the colon punctuation mark is currently not supported as a special character for use in text searching; therefore, it is cumbersome to search for bugs which contain the colon as part of the text string, at least in our specific case.

