It would be helpful for transition from dev, tst, and prod if there was a method to run backup/restore of data that is done in the gui via the Import & Export option at the command line.  This would allow customers and developers on your end to update the data periodically.  The attachments can already be done via a variety of methods, but adding that as part of the backup/restore method would be nice too.

This is an enhancement request that would allow working with attachments much more convenient. Now if you add an attachment to JIRA issue it will only be listed above but it is very tough and confusing to guess which attachment was added where. Imagine that you work on a customer issue and support adds 3 log files at 3 different times into JIRA. You always comment: Get me the log and they comment Here it is. Then you see 3 attachments called CustomerLog or so. Now it is difficult to guess which log is which. You must compare the attachment dates to the comment dates which may be tricky if this is within one day. Also you always need to scroll down and up for it. I know that you have the option to add a comment referencing the attachment but nobody is doing that because it requires additional work. After adding the attachment you need to write an extra comment and manually create the reference which means manually typing the file name of the attachment and checking that you really did it correctly. This is so tedious that nobody is doing that which means that there is either a big mess in attachments or people put content directly to comments rather than using attachments which makes it really hard to scroll the issue all the way down.

Could such a feature be added that when attaching a file to a JIRA issue it would automatically add a comment of the form
{noformat}
The user XY attached the file [^File name]
{noformat}

That would make it much easier to work with attachments.

